{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaafb1bcf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7628"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7628"},"text":"§ 7628.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Airplane parts and accessories: civilian flying schools","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of the Army may sell, to civilian flying schools at which personnel of the Department of the Army or the Department of the Air Force are receiving flight training under contracts requiring these schools to maintain and repair airplanes of the Army furnished to them for flight training, the spare parts and accessories needed for those repairs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaafb1bd0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/259"},"text":"70A Stat. 259","children":[],"tail":", § 4628; renumbered § 7628, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s808/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1839"},"text":"132 Stat. 1839","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaafb1bd1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idaafb1bd2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idaafb1bd3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tai